{"id":19654,"date":"2024-01-29T05:10:00","date_gmt":"2023-08-29T05:10:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=19654"},"modified":"2022-11-29T11:32:59","modified_gmt":"2022-11-29T06:02:59","slug":"how-to-clean-countertops","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/how-to-clean-countertops\/","title":{"rendered":"Easy Hacks To Clean All Types Of Kitchen Countertops"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/\">DesignCafe\u2019s<\/a> comprehensive list of cleaning hacks will keep your kitchen countertops dazzling.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Does kitchen countertop cleaning give you nightmares? Does it feel like you are spending a better part of your life keeping the kitchen tidy without it making any difference? Are you always looking for answers to how to clean kitchen countertops? Does walking into your neighbour\u2019s home give you kitchen envy? You are not alone.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/10-different-types-of-kitchen-countertops\/\">Kitchen countertops<\/a> can make the most of us like hamsters on a wheel \u2014 the job is never ending and seems pointless. It\u2019s natural to feel defeated by it. After all, the kitchen is a high-traffic area, especially since many of us are working from home. But fret not. We have just what you need \u2014 not a genie that will clean up your kitchen countertops but delightful hacks that will turn you into that genie that you so wish for. Let\u2019s go.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Before You Clean The Kitchen Countertop<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>First, a few words of caution. Here are some common mistakes homeowners make while cleaning their kitchen countertops. Do avoid them to keep your countertop pretty and effective.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Avoid acidic cleaners. Using the same cleaning agent over every surface is appealing, but it has its cons. Vinegar and similar acidic cleaners make stone and granite kitchen countertops lose their lustre. Even bleach tends to dull the stone countertops. Check your all-purpose cleaner ingredients. If it has citric acid, avoid it at all costs.<\/li><li>Not sealing the stone countertops. Water and stains can ruin your stone kitchen countertop. Sealing the countertop will ensure they stay pretty for longer. If a few drops of water percolate into the stone countertop, sealing is due. Spritz sealing spray on the countertop with a soft cloth, rub it in, and you are done.\u00a0<\/li><li>Not disinfecting. The kitchen counters are a haven for germs with constant moisture and high touch frequency. Spray a disinfectant, especially after using raw eggs and meat, let it sit for the designated time (check your disinfectant container for \u2018dwell time\u2019), and wipe it off with a clean cloth.\u00a0<\/li><li>Not cleaning the cleaning cloths. Wash and dry them out after every cleaning to avoid transferring the germs to other areas. Replace microfibre cloths or sponges after a month\u2019s use.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29111206\/common-mistakes-while-cleaning-kitchen-countertops.jpg\" alt=\"Common mistakes while cleaning kitchen countertops\" class=\"wp-image-39720\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29111206\/common-mistakes-while-cleaning-kitchen-countertops.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29111206\/common-mistakes-while-cleaning-kitchen-countertops-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29111206\/common-mistakes-while-cleaning-kitchen-countertops-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29111206\/common-mistakes-while-cleaning-kitchen-countertops-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Avoid acidic cleaners for your kitchen countertops<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1080\" height=\"2029\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29111015\/materials-for-cleaning-kitchen-countertops.jpg\" alt=\"Materials for cleaning kitchen countertops\" class=\"wp-image-39719\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29111015\/materials-for-cleaning-kitchen-countertops.jpg 1080w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29111015\/materials-for-cleaning-kitchen-countertops-160x300.jpg 160w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29111015\/materials-for-cleaning-kitchen-countertops-545x1024.jpg 545w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29111015\/materials-for-cleaning-kitchen-countertops-768x1443.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29111015\/materials-for-cleaning-kitchen-countertops-818x1536.jpg 818w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29111015\/materials-for-cleaning-kitchen-countertops-150x282.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How To Clean Quartz Kitchen Countertops<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Wondering how to clean Caesarstone quartz countertops or how to clean Cambria quartz countertops? It\u2019s pretty simple. What applies to one applies to the other. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/quartz-countertops\/\">Quartz kitchen countertops<\/a> are non-porous and durable. Accidental oil spills and stains are no cause to worry. Just ensure you are using non-abrasive and mild cleaning supplies.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Tools you need: <\/strong>Dish soap, water, non-abrasive glass cleaner, microfibre cloth<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What to do: <\/strong>Simply wipe off for regular cleaning. When you\u2019re dealing with stains, use soap, water and a microfibre cloth. Use a non-abrasive glass cleaner if handling tough stains. Yes, it is this simple to take care of this kitchen countertop material.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110931\/quartz-kitchen-countertops-cleaning.jpg\" alt=\"Quartz kitchen countertops cleaning are low-maintenance\" class=\"wp-image-39718\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110931\/quartz-kitchen-countertops-cleaning.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110931\/quartz-kitchen-countertops-cleaning-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110931\/quartz-kitchen-countertops-cleaning-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110931\/quartz-kitchen-countertops-cleaning-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Quartz kitchen countertops are low-maintenance<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Do you know whats trending for your kitchen countertops\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/17140915\/do-you-know-whats-trending-for-your-kitchen-countertops.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How To Clean Granite Kitchen Countertops<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Tools you need: <\/strong>Dish soap, water, non-abrasive glass cleaner, microfibre cloth, hydrogen peroxide, baking soda<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What to do: <\/strong>Granite countertops clean up well with regular soap and water. For tougher stains, use a paste made of baking soda and wipe it off after some time. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/granite-countertops\/\">Granite kitchen countertops<\/a> do well with annual resealing.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Word of caution: Do not use acidic cleaners or bleach. This will help to maintain the shine and durability of granite countertops in the kitchen.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110914\/how-to-clean-granite-countertops.jpg\" alt=\"Granite countertops clean up well with regular soap and water\" class=\"wp-image-39715\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110914\/how-to-clean-granite-countertops.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110914\/how-to-clean-granite-countertops-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110914\/how-to-clean-granite-countertops-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110914\/how-to-clean-granite-countertops-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Granite kitchen countertops dazzle after cleaning<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How To Clean And Polish Marble Kitchen Countertops<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Marble responds almost immediately to anything acidic. So, handle the lemons, wine, vinegar, and tomatoes with care. Accidental spills should be immediately wiped off. Neutralise their acidic reaction by sprinkling baking soda.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Tools you need: <\/strong>Dish soap, water, non-abrasive glass cleaner, microfibre cloth, hydrogen peroxide (12%), baking soda, tape and plastic (if you are getting really intense about stain removal)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What to do: <\/strong>The simple harmony between microfibre cloth, warm water, and dish soap works wonders for the everyday cleaning of marble kitchen countertops. For stubborn stains, apply a paste of baking soda or hydrogen peroxide with water. Let it sit overnight under plastic sealed with tape. Wipe off the paste. Repeat if needed. Remember that you can use hydrogen peroxide on light-coloured marble only. Do not use it for cleaning darker marble countertops. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/marble-kitchen-countertops\/\">Marble kitchen countertops<\/a> need resealing about every six months, so remember to do that regularly.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110908\/how-to-clean-and-polish-marble-countertops.jpg\" alt=\"Clean up and polish marble countertops with a microfibre cloth, warm water, and dish soap work wonders\" class=\"wp-image-39714\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110908\/how-to-clean-and-polish-marble-countertops.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110908\/how-to-clean-and-polish-marble-countertops-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110908\/how-to-clean-and-polish-marble-countertops-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110908\/how-to-clean-and-polish-marble-countertops-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A clean marble kitchen countertop is a delight<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How To Clean Laminate Kitchen Countertops<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Tools you need: <\/strong>Regular cleaner (mild) and baking soda<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What to do: <\/strong>A damp, soft, clean cloth is enough to clean laminate tops. Use a mild detergent and avoid strong acid or alkali products. For stain removal, make a baking soda and water paste, apply it to the stain and wipe it off after five minutes. Do not use steel or abrasive scrubs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110926\/how-to-clean-laminate-countertops.jpg\" alt=\"Clean laminate countertops with mild soap and avoid strong acid or alkali products\" class=\"wp-image-39717\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110926\/how-to-clean-laminate-countertops.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110926\/how-to-clean-laminate-countertops-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110926\/how-to-clean-laminate-countertops-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/29110926\/how-to-clean-laminate-countertops-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Mild soap is enough for laminate kitchen countertops<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It is quicker to run through a regular kitchen countertop cleaning ritual, but deep cleaning needs forethought and patience. Getting a handsome clean isn\u2019t just about spraying, wiping, and walking away. You can achieve professional cleaning for your kitchen countertops with a few tools and intelligent methods. Follow our fixes to clean your kitchen countertops effectively and without much elbow grease.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n               